  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is BUPA Global worth the extra cost over AXA Global?</h3>
  <p>
    For most healthy expats, no. AXA provides comprehensive coverage at 30-40% lower premiums. BUPA is worth the premium if you specifically need their mental health coverage, want pre-existing conditions underwritten, or prioritize exceptional service over cost savings.
  </p>

  <h3>Which provider has better mental health coverage?</h3>
  <p>
    BUPA Global has significantly better mental health coverage—it's one of their key differentiators. More generous session limits, better coverage terms, and a genuine emphasis on mental health benefits. If mental health is important, BUPA is the clear choice.
  </p>

  <h3>How do pre-existing conditions work with each provider?</h3>
  <p>
    AXA uses moratorium underwriting—pre-existing conditions are automatically excluded until you go claim-free for a period (usually 2-5 years). BUPA uses full medical underwriting—they review your health history and may cover well-managed conditions from day one, exclude specific conditions, or apply premium loadings. <a href="/best/expat-health-insurance" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 underline">Get quotes from both</a> to see what terms each offers for your situation.
  </p>

  <h3>Does BUPA's no-claims discount offset their higher premiums?</h3>
  <p>
    Partially, for consistently healthy members. If you maintain no-claims status for years, the discounts accumulate and can reduce the price gap. But if you make claims, you lose the discount while still paying higher base premiums. For most people, the discount doesn't fully close the gap.
  </p>

  <h3>Which provider is better for families?</h3>
  <p>
    Both serve families well. AXA offers significant cost savings—potentially $3,600-6,000 annually for a family. BUPA offers better mental health coverage for any family member who might need it and superior service. For healthy families, AXA's savings are compelling. For families with specific needs BUPA serves, the premium may be justified.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I switch between these providers?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, at annual renewal. However, conditions that developed while on your previous policy become pre-existing for the new insurer. If you've developed health issues, switching carefully—particularly to AXA's moratorium underwriting, which would exclude your new conditions.
  </p>

